<p><a name="Companion_book" id="Companion_book"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Manufacturing_Consent:_Noam_Chomsky_and_the_Media&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1" title="Edit section: Companion book">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Companion book</span></h2>
<p>Mark Achbar edited a companion book of the same name. It features a copy of the script annotated with excerpts from referenced and relevant materials as well as several comments from Chomsky interspersed throughout. Eighteen "Philosopher All-Stars" <a href="/wiki/Baseball_card" title="Baseball card">baseball cards</a> (as seen in the film) are also included. On the back of each card it includes a short summary of the person, some of their major works and a series of quotations attributed to the individual. The people featured as cards in the set are: <a href="/wiki/Ren%C3%A9_Descartes" title="René Descartes">René Descartes</a>, <a href="/wiki/Jean-Jacques_Rousseau" title="Jean-Jacques Rousseau">Jean-Jacques Rousseau</a>, <a href="/wiki/Voltaire" title="Voltaire">Voltaire</a>, <a href="/wiki/Mary_Wollstonecraft" title="Mary Wollstonecraft">Mary Wollstonecraft</a>, <a href="/wiki/Wilhelm_von_Humboldt" title="Wilhelm von Humboldt">Wilhelm von Humboldt</a>, <a href="/wiki/Pierre_Joseph_Proudhon" title="Pierre Joseph Proudhon" class="mw-redirect">Pierre Joseph Proudhon</a>, <a href="/wiki/Sojourner_Truth" title="Sojourner Truth">Sojourner Truth</a>, <a href="/wiki/Karl_Marx" title="Karl Marx">Karl Marx</a>, <a href="/wiki/Sitting_Bull" title="Sitting Bull">Sitting Bull</a>, <a href="/wiki/Rosa_Luxemburg" title="Rosa Luxemburg">Rosa Luxemburg</a>, <a href="/wiki/Peter_Kropotkin" title="Peter Kropotkin">Peter Kropotkin</a>, <a href="/wiki/Emma_Goldman" title="Emma Goldman">Emma Goldman</a>, <a href="/wiki/Gandhi" title="Gandhi" class="mw-redirect">Gandhi</a>, <a href="/wiki/Martin_Luther_King,_Jr." title="Martin Luther King, Jr.">Martin Luther King, Jr.</a>, <a href="/wiki/Bertrand_Russell" title="Bertrand Russell">Bertrand Russell</a>, <a href="/wiki/Michel_Foucault" title="Michel Foucault">Michel Foucault</a>, and <a href="/wiki/Avram_Noam_Chomsky" title="Avram Noam Chomsky" class="mw-redirect">Avram Noam Chomsky</a>. The book made the national bestseller list in Canada.</p>
<p>The first half of the book, hyperlinked to the relevant portions of the film's audio, is <a href="http://zmag.org/chomsky/mc/" class="external text" title="http://zmag.org/chomsky/mc/" rel="nofollow">available online</a> from <i><a href="/wiki/Z_Magazine" title="Z Magazine" class="mw-redirect">Z Magazine</a></i>.</p>
